

static variable:

class Employee{
  static String company = "infosys";
  int id;
}
Employee e1 = new Employee();
Employee e2 = new Employee();

System.out.println(e1.company); // Infosys
System.out.println(e2.company); // Infosys


only one copy of company exist
Static vairale are shared across all objects!

Static method: Static methods can be called without creating an object.

class Utils {
    static void printMsg() {
        System.out.println("Hello");
    }
}

we can call without object

Utils.printMsg(); is possible

3. STATIC BLOCK
---------------

class Test {
    static {
        System.out.println("Static block executed");
    }

    public static void main(String[] args) {
        System.out.println("Main method");
    }
}

output:
Static block executed
Main method

used for initilaze static data  &
loading driver
static vlock execute once when the class is loaded

